        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 2:48PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
El Porvenir, or 11 miles northwest of Las Vegas, moving southeast at
5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
El Porvenir, Montezuma, Gallinas, Mineral Hill and San Geronimo.

This includes the following highways...
State Road 518 between Mile Markers 6 and 7.
State Road 283 between Mile Markers 8 and 12...and
near Mile Marker 14.
State Road 65 between Mile Markers 5 and 14.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
